<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-02-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-02-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="405" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d405">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Ambassador</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-02-28"><hi rend="italic">February 28,
                                    1911</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 167.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I inclose a copy of a letter from the
                            Treasury Department in which a suggestion is made, etc. [repeating the
                            substance of the foregoing letter].</p>
                        <p>The Department will be gratified if you will take up the matter with the
                            Italian Government ind report its views regarding it.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">P. C. Knox.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>